description:
Create minimal main.zig that verifies DuckDB integration.

**File:** `zig/src/main.zig`

**Functionality:**
1. Set up Zig 0.15.2 buffered I/O (`.interface` pattern)
2. Open in-memory DuckDB via zuckdb
3. Execute `SELECT 1` to verify connection
4. Print result and exit

**Code pattern:**
```zig
const zuckdb = @import("zuckdb");

pub fn main() !void {
    var gpa = std.heap.GeneralPurposeAllocator(.{}){};
    defer _ = gpa.deinit();

    // Zig 0.15.2 I/O
    const stdout_file = std.fs.File.stdout();
    var stdout_buf: [4096]u8 = undefined;
    var stdout_writer = stdout_file.writer(&stdout_buf);
    const stdout = &stdout_writer.interface;
    defer stdout.flush() catch {};

    // DuckDB test
    var db = try zuckdb.DB.init(null, .{});
    defer db.deinit();
    var conn = try db.conn();
    defer conn.deinit();

    try stdout.print("DuckDB connection successful\\n", .{});
}
```

**Verification:**
```bash
cd zig && zig build run
# Should print "DuckDB connection successful"
```

**Acceptance criteria:**
- Binary compiles and runs
- DuckDB opens without error
- No memory leaks (GPA reports clean)
